<TITLE> Govt absorbs 2713 education jobs into revenue </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Mustak Ahmed bdnews24.com correspondent Dhaka, May 7 (bdnews24.com)The government has absorbed 2,173 redundant development jobs under education ministry into revenue budget, education minister Nurul Islam Nahid told bdnews24.com on Thursday. A finance ministry order transferred these posts of four education ministry development projects at Upazilas to the revenue head following project completion. "The government has taken up the step to resolve problems over these posts," Nahid said. The jobs include 698 from female secondary school assistant project, 1060 from female secondary stipend project, 256 from secondary education development project, 93 from female secondary education stipend project and 66 posts from implementation unit of these projects. The order said these employees will be working with Upazila secondary education offices. bd
